#. type: Title =
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Workflow integration: Aperture\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:9
msgid ""
"Aperture (from Apple) allows you to select another application as an "
"\"external editor\" for editing your photos. You can configure LightZone to "
"be such an editor. Additionally, LightZone integrates seamlessly with "
"Aperture via the [Direct Save](Preferences.html#Preferences-Direct_Save)  "
"preference."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** The information provided here is accurate as of Aperture\n"
"version 1.5.3 but may need to change for future versions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "To configure Aperture to work with LightZone:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:18
msgid ""
"Select Aperture \\> Preferences... (the Preferences dialog will appear) and "
"refer to the Output section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:20
msgid "Under External Image Editor, click the Choose... button."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:22
msgid "Navigate to and select LightZone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:24
msgid "For External Editor File Format, select TIFF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:26 Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:52
msgid "Close the Preferences dialog."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:31
msgid ""
"[![image](images/AppleScriptAppIcon.png)](help:runscript='LightZone_Help/scripts/Set_Aperture_Prefs.scpt')  "
"Alternatively, you can click the AppleScript icon to the left to configure "
"Aperture automatically for you now. (If Aperture is running, you must quit "
"it first.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:33
#, no-wrap
msgid " When using an external editor, Aperture:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:35
msgid "Creates a TIFF copy of your photo (with corrections applied)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:38
msgid ""
"Adds this TIFF copy to the current Aperture library as a version of the "
"original."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:40
msgid "Gives this TIFF copy to the external editor to edit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "To configure LightZone to work with Aperture:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:46
msgid "Select LightZone \\> Preferences... (The Preferences dialog will appear.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:50
msgid ""
"Make sure the [Direct Save](Preferences.html#Preferences-Direct_Save) "
"check-box is checked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:55
msgid ""
"Now that everything has been configured, you can select one of your photos "
"in Aperture and edit it in LightZone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "To edit your photo in LightZone from Aperture:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:60
msgid "In Aperture, select the photo you want to edit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:63
msgid ""
"Select Images \\> Open With External Editor. (LightZone will launch and open "
"the TIFF copy of your photo.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:66
msgid ""
"In LightZone, edit the TIFF copy of your photo to your liking as you would "
"any photo."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4.  '
#: Integration-Aperture.markdown.txt:70
msgid ""
"Select File \\> Save to Aperture. (LightZone will save your edited photo "
"back to the TIFF copy overwriting it, switch back to Aperture, and Aperture "
"will reload the now edited TIFF copy of your photo.)"
msgstr ""

